Node.Notes: "Struck your palms" is a gesture of concluding an agreement.
These words may be taken as a continuation of the teacher's sarcastic comments or a quotation of the response of the sluggard (which are used against the sluggard).
In light of vs. 12 and 14, these three gestures are most likely signs of insincerity/deceit.

Uncertain. Loaf of bread may signify prostitute's hire (supported by LXX) or poverty to which the man is reduced. Overall sense either comparison of little cost (a loaf of bread) to great cost (death) or great cost (poverty) to ultimate cost (death) in involvement with a prostitute versus an adulteress.
